  'jira',
  'issue-detail',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: jira\nscreen: issue-detail\nversion: "Cloud 2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Jira: Issue Detail Page\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Project > Board/Backlog > [Issue Key] (e.g., PROJ-123), or via /browse/PROJ-123\n\n## Overview\nThe issue detail page is the central workspace for viewing and managing a single Jira issue (story, task, bug, epic, or subtask). It displays the issue summary, description, status, assignee, and all metadata fields. The right sidebar shows the detail panel with status transitions, assignment, priority, labels, and sprint. Below the description, the activity section shows comments, history, and worklog entries.\n\n## Key Fields\n- **Summary**: The issue title displayed at the top of the page. Click to edit inline.\n- **Status**: Displayed as a colored badge. Click to transition (e.g., To Do > In Progress > Done).\n- **Assignee**: Avatar and name. Click to reassign. "Assign to me" shortcut available.\n- **Reporter**: The person who created the issue. Typically auto-set but editable.\n- **Priority**: Icon + label. Values: Highest, High, Medium, Low, Lowest.\n- **Type**: Issue type icon (Story, Bug, Task, Epic, Subtask). Set at creation, rarely changed.\n- **Sprint**: Which sprint the issue belongs to. Editable from the detail panel.\n- **Story Points / Estimate**: Numeric estimate field. Click to edit.\n- **Labels**: Tag-style labels for cross-cutting categorization.\n- **Fix Version**: Target release version.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Transition Status**: Click the status badge to open the transition dropdown. Available transitions depend on the workflow.\n- **Add Comment**: Scroll to the activity section and type in the comment box. Supports @mentions, /commands, and rich formatting.\n- **Attach Files**: Drag and drop files onto the issue, or click the attachment icon.\n- **Link Issue**: Create relationships: blocks, is blocked by, relates to, duplicates, etc.\n- **Create Subtask**: Click "Create subtask" to break the issue into smaller work items.\n- **Log Work**: Record time spent on the issue for time tracking.\n- **Move Issue**: Transfer to a different project while preserving history.\n\n## Activity Section\n- **Comments**: Threaded discussion with @mentions and emoji reactions.\n- **History**: Audit log of all field changes with timestamps and authors.\n- **Worklog**: Time entries logged against the issue.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Status badge: `[data-testid="issue.views.issue-base.foundation.status.status-field-wrapper"]`\n- Assignee field: `[data-testid="issue.views.issue-base.foundation.assignee.assignee-field"]`\n- Comment input: `[data-testid="issue.activity.comment"]`\n- Priority field: `[data-testid="issue.views.issue-base.foundation.priority.priority-field"]`\n- Summary heading: `[data-testid="issue.views.issue-base.foundation.summary.heading"]`',
  '{"Status Badge": "[data-testid=\"issue.views.issue-base.foundation.status.status-field-wrapper\"]", "Assignee": "[data-testid=\"issue.views.issue-base.foundation.assignee.assignee-field\"]", "Comment Input": "[data-testid=\"issue.activity.comment\"]", "Priority": "[data-testid=\"issue.views.issue-base.foundation.priority.priority-field\"]", "Summary": "[data-testid=\"issue.views.issue-base.foundation.summary.heading\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'jira',
  'board',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: jira\nscreen: board\nversion: "Cloud 2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Jira: Board View\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Project > Board, or /jira/software/projects/[KEY]/boards/[ID]\n\n## Overview\nThe board view is a Kanban or Scrum board that visualizes issues as cards organized into columns representing workflow statuses. In Scrum projects, the board shows only the active sprint''s issues. In Kanban projects, it shows all issues within configured column constraints. Cards can be dragged between columns to transition their status.\n\n## Key Features\n- **Columns**: Each column maps to one or more workflow statuses (e.g., To Do, In Progress, In Review, Done). Column names and mappings are configurable in board settings.\n- **Issue Cards**: Cards display the issue key, summary, assignee avatar, priority icon, and story points. Card layout is customizable.\n- **Swimlanes**: Horizontal groupings that divide the board by assignee, epic, priority, or no grouping.\n- **WIP Limits**: Kanban boards can set maximum issue counts per column. Columns exceeding the limit are highlighted in red.\n- **Quick Filters**: Toggle buttons at the top to filter by label, assignee, issue type, or custom JQL.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Drag and Drop**: Move an issue card between columns to change its status. This triggers workflow transitions.\n- **Create Issue**: Click "+" at the bottom of any column to create a new issue in that status.\n- **Open Issue**: Click an issue card to open the detail panel on the right side (or navigate to the full issue page).\n- **Sprint Actions** (Scrum only): "Complete Sprint" button finishes the current sprint and moves incomplete issues to the backlog or next sprint.\n- **Board Settings**: Configure columns, swimlanes, quick filters, card layout, and estimation settings.\n- **Filter by Assignee**: Click an avatar in the filter bar to show only that person''s issues.\n\n## Board Configuration\n- **Column Mapping**: Map workflow statuses to board columns. Multiple statuses can map to one column.\n- **Card Layout**: Choose which fields appear on issue cards (priority, labels, due date, etc.).\n- **Quick Filters**: Define JQL-based filter toggles for common views.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Board container: `[data-testid="software-board.board"]`\n- Board column: `[data-testid="software-board.board-container.board.column-header"]`\n- Issue card: `[data-testid="software-board.board-container.board.card-container"]`\n- Quick filters: `[data-testid="software-board.header.quick-filters"]`\n- Create issue input: `[data-testid="software-board.board-container.board.card-list.card.create-issue"]`',
  '{"Board Container": "[data-testid=\"software-board.board\"]", "Column Header": "[data-testid=\"software-board.board-container.board.column-header\"]", "Issue Card": "[data-testid=\"software-board.board-container.board.card-container\"]", "Quick Filters": "[data-testid=\"software-board.header.quick-filters\"]", "Create Issue": "[data-testid=\"software-board.board-container.board.card-list.card.create-issue\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'jira',
  'backlog',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: jira\nscreen: backlog\nversion: "Cloud 2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Jira: Backlog View\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Project > Backlog, or /jira/software/projects/[KEY]/backlog\n\n## Overview\nThe backlog view shows all issues in a project organized into sprints (for Scrum) or a prioritized list (for Kanban). The top section shows the active sprint, followed by future sprints, with the unassigned backlog at the bottom. Issues can be dragged between sprints or reordered within a sprint to set priority.\n\n## Key Features\n- **Sprint Sections**: Collapsible sections for each sprint showing sprint name, date range, issue count, and story point total.\n- **Backlog Section**: The bottom section holds unassigned issues not yet committed to a sprint.\n- **Issue Rows**: Each row shows issue key, type icon, summary, priority, assignee, story points, and status.\n- **Epic Panel**: Toggle the epic panel on the left to filter backlog by epic. Color-coded epic bars appear on issue rows.\n- **Estimation**: Inline story point editing by clicking the estimate badge on each issue row.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Create Sprint**: Click "Create sprint" to add a new empty sprint section.\n- **Start Sprint**: Set the sprint goal, date range, and activate it. Moves to the board view.\n- **Drag to Sprint**: Drag issues from the backlog into a sprint section, or between sprints.\n- **Reorder**: Drag issues up/down within a sprint or backlog to set relative priority (top = highest).\n- **Create Issue**: Click "Create issue" at the bottom of any section to add a new issue inline.\n- **Right-Click Context Menu**: Access quick actions: assign, change priority, move to sprint, split issue, flag, or delete.\n- **Bulk Select**: Hold Shift or Cmd/Ctrl to select multiple issues, then drag or use context menu for bulk operations.\n\n## Sprint Planning\n- **Sprint Goal**: Text field describing what the sprint aims to achieve.\n- **Capacity**: Compare story point total against team velocity to avoid overcommitting.\n- **Scope Indicators**: Visual indicators show if a sprint is over or under capacity.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Backlog container: `[data-testid="software-backlog.backlog-content"]`\n- Sprint header: `[data-testid="software-backlog.sprint-header"]`\n- Create sprint button: `[data-testid="software-backlog.create-sprint-button"]`\n- Issue row: `[data-testid="software-backlog.backlog-content.card"]`\n- Epic panel toggle: `[data-testid="software-backlog.epic-panel-toggle"]`',
  '{"Backlog Container": "[data-testid=\"software-backlog.backlog-content\"]", "Sprint Header": "[data-testid=\"software-backlog.sprint-header\"]", "Create Sprint": "[data-testid=\"software-backlog.create-sprint-button\"]", "Issue Row": "[data-testid=\"software-backlog.backlog-content.card\"]", "Epic Panel": "[data-testid=\"software-backlog.epic-panel-toggle\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'jira',
  'roadmap',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: jira\nscreen: roadmap\nversion: "Cloud 2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Jira: Roadmap (Timeline) View\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Project > Timeline/Roadmap, or /jira/software/projects/[KEY]/roadmap\n\n## Overview\nThe roadmap view provides a Gantt-chart-style timeline of epics and their child issues. Epics are displayed as horizontal bars spanning their start and due dates, with child issues nested beneath. This view is ideal for long-term planning, tracking epic progress, and communicating delivery timelines to stakeholders.\n\n## Key Features\n- **Epic Bars**: Horizontal bars showing each epic''s date range. Bar color indicates the epic''s color label. Bar fill shows progress (percentage of child issues completed).\n- **Child Issues**: Expand an epic to see its child issues listed below with their own date ranges.\n- **Time Scale**: Toggle between weeks, months, and quarters using the zoom control at the top right.\n- **Today Marker**: Vertical line indicating the current date for quick orientation.\n- **Dependencies**: Lines connecting related epics or issues to visualize blocking relationships.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Create Epic**: Click "+ Create epic" at the bottom of the list or click an empty area on the timeline.\n- **Create Child Issue**: Click "+" on an expanded epic row to add a child issue.\n- **Adjust Dates**: Drag the left or right edge of an epic bar to change start/due dates. Drag the entire bar to shift both dates.\n- **Set Dependencies**: Draw a line from one epic to another to create a dependency link.\n- **Filter**: Use the search and filter bar to narrow by status, assignee, label, or text.\n- **Share Roadmap**: Export or share a read-only link for stakeholders who don''t have Jira access.\n\n## Progress Tracking\n- **Epic Progress Bar**: Shows the percentage of child issues in "Done" status.\n- **Status Counts**: Hover over an epic to see the breakdown of To Do, In Progress, and Done issues.\n- **Overdue Indicators**: Epics past their due date with incomplete work are highlighted.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Roadmap container: `[data-testid="roadmap.page"]`\n- Epic row: `[data-testid="roadmap.epic-row"]`\n- Create epic button: `[data-testid="roadmap.create-epic-button"]`\n- Time scale toggle: `[data-testid="roadmap.time-scale-toggle"]`\n- Filter bar: `[data-testid="roadmap.filter-bar"]`',
  '{"Roadmap Container": "[data-testid=\"roadmap.page\"]", "Epic Row": "[data-testid=\"roadmap.epic-row\"]", "Create Epic": "[data-testid=\"roadmap.create-epic-button\"]", "Time Scale": "[data-testid=\"roadmap.time-scale-toggle\"]", "Filter Bar": "[data-testid=\"roadmap.filter-bar\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'jira',
  'issue-list',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: jira\nscreen: issue-list\nversion: "Cloud 2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Jira: Issue List View\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Project > List, or /jira/software/projects/[KEY]/list\n\n## Overview\nThe issue list view shows all project issues in a flat, sortable table format. Unlike the board view, it displays issues regardless of sprint assignment and provides more detail per row. This view is useful for triaging, bulk editing, and detailed filtering. It supports inline editing of most fields.\n\n## Key Features\n- **Table Columns**: Customizable columns including Key, Summary, Type, Status, Priority, Assignee, Reporter, Created, Updated, Story Points, Sprint, Labels, and Fix Version.\n- **Sorting**: Click any column header to sort ascending or descending. Multiple column sort is supported.\n- **Grouping**: Group issues by status, assignee, priority, sprint, or epic using the "Group by" dropdown.\n- **Inline Editing**: Click most fields directly in the table to edit them without opening the issue.\n- **JQL Filter Bar**: Write or modify JQL (Jira Query Language) queries to filter the issue list precisely.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Create Issue**: Click "Create" button in the top bar to open the issue creation dialog.\n- **Bulk Change**: Select multiple issues with checkboxes, then use "Bulk change" to update status, assignee, priority, or other fields in batch.\n- **Export**: Export the filtered list to CSV or printable format.\n- **Save Filter**: Save the current JQL query as a named filter for reuse.\n- **Share View**: Copy a link to the current filtered view or share it with teammates.\n- **Column Configuration**: Click the column header dropdown to add, remove, or reorder columns.\n\n## Filtering\n- **Basic Filters**: Dropdowns for Type, Status, Assignee, and Label above the table.\n- **JQL Mode**: Toggle to advanced JQL for complex queries like `status changed FROM "In Progress" AFTER -7d`.\n- **Text Search**: Search within issue summaries and descriptions.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- List container: `[data-testid="list-view.container"]`\n- Issue row: `[data-testid="list-view.list-item"]`\n- Create button: `[data-testid="list-view.create-button"]`\n- Filter bar: `[data-testid="list-view.filter-bar"]`\n- Column header: `[data-testid="list-view.column-header"]`',
  '{"List Container": "[data-testid=\"list-view.container\"]", "Issue Row": "[data-testid=\"list-view.list-item\"]", "Create Button": "[data-testid=\"list-view.create-button\"]", "Filter Bar": "[data-testid=\"list-view.filter-bar\"]", "Column Header": "[data-testid=\"list-view.column-header\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'jira',
  'dashboard',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: jira\nscreen: dashboard\nversion: "Cloud 2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Jira: Dashboard\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Dashboards (top navigation), or /jira/dashboards\n\n## Overview\nThe Jira dashboard is a customizable homepage that displays gadgets. Each user can create multiple dashboards and set one as their default. Dashboards support a two-column layout where gadgets can be arranged by dragging.\n\n## Common Gadgets\n- **Assigned to Me**: List of issues currently assigned to you, sorted by priority.\n- **Activity Stream**: Real-time feed of recent activity across projects.\n- **Filter Results**: Display issues matching a saved JQL filter as a table.\n- **Pie Chart**: Visual breakdown of issues by any field.\n- **Created vs Resolved**: Line chart comparing issue creation rate to resolution rate over time.\n- **Sprint Burndown**: Shows remaining work in the active sprint against the ideal burndown line.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Add Gadget**: Click "Add gadget" to browse and add new gadgets to the dashboard.\n- **Edit Layout**: Enter edit mode to drag, resize, and configure gadgets.\n- **Create Dashboard**: Click "Create dashboard" and choose blank or copy from an existing one.\n- **Set as Default**: Star a dashboard to make it your landing page.\n- **Share Dashboard**: Configure visibility for teams, projects, or the whole org.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Dashboard container: `#ak-main-content`\n- Add gadget button: `[data-testid="dashboard.add-gadget-button"]`\n- Gadget frame: `[data-testid="dashboard.gadget-frame"]`\n- Dashboard selector: `[data-testid="dashboard.dashboard-selector"]`\n- Edit layout button: `[data-testid="dashboard.edit-button"]`',
  '{"Dashboard Container": "#ak-main-content", "Add Gadget": "[data-testid=\"dashboard.add-gadget-button\"]", "Gadget Frame": "[data-testid=\"dashboard.gadget-frame\"]", "Dashboard Selector": "[data-testid=\"dashboard.dashboard-selector\"]", "Edit Layout": "[data-testid=\"dashboard.edit-button\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'jira',
  'project-list',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: jira\nscreen: project-list\nversion: "Cloud 2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Jira: Project List\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Projects (top navigation), or /jira/projects\n\n## Overview\nThe project list page shows all Jira projects the current user has access to. Each project row displays the project name, key, type (Software, Service Management, Business), lead, and category.\n\n## Key Features\n- **Project Cards/List**: Toggle between card view and list view.\n- **Search**: Search projects by name or key.\n- **Starred Projects**: Star frequently used projects for quick access.\n- **Project Type Filter**: Filter by Software, Service Management, or Business project types.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Open Project**: Click a project to navigate to its board view.\n- **Create Project**: Click "Create project" to start the project creation wizard.\n- **Star Project**: Click the star icon to pin a project to your sidebar.\n- **Project Settings**: Click the three-dot menu to access settings and permissions.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Project list container: `[data-testid="project-list.container"]`\n- Project row: `[data-testid="project-list.project-row"]`\n- Create project button: `[data-testid="project-list.create-project-button"]`\n- Search input: `[data-testid="project-list.search-input"]`\n- Star button: `[data-testid="project-list.star-button"]`',
  '{"Project List": "[data-testid=\"project-list.container\"]", "Project Row": "[data-testid=\"project-list.project-row\"]", "Create Project": "[data-testid=\"project-list.create-project-button\"]", "Search Input": "[data-testid=\"project-list.search-input\"]", "Star Button": "[data-testid=\"project-list.star-button\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'jira',
  'unknown-jira',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: jira\nscreen: unknown-jira\nversion: "Cloud 2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Jira: General Navigation\n\n## Overview\nThis page covers general Jira Cloud navigation and features that apply across multiple screens.\n\n## Global Navigation\n- **Top Bar**: Contains the Jira logo (home), Projects dropdown, Filters dropdown, Dashboards dropdown, People dropdown, Apps dropdown, Create button, and Search.\n- **Search**: Click the search icon or press `/` to open global search.\n- **Create Button**: Blue "Create" button in the top bar opens the issue creation dialog from anywhere.\n- **Notifications**: Bell icon shows recent notifications.\n\n## Sidebar Navigation\n- **Project Sidebar**: Board, Backlog, Roadmap/Timeline, List, Code, Deployments, Project Pages, and Project Settings.\n\n## Common Keyboard Shortcuts\n- **C**: Create new issue\n- **/** : Open global search\n- **G then B**: Go to board\n- **G then K**: Go to backlog\n- **J / K**: Navigate between issues\n- **E**: Edit issue\n- **M**: Assign to me\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Top navigation: `[data-ds--page-layout--slot="top-navigation"]`\n- Main content: `#ak-main-content`\n- Sidebar: `[data-ds--page-layout--slot="left-sidebar"]`\n- Create button: `[data-testid="navigation-apps-create-button"]`\n- Search: `[data-testid="navigation-apps-search-button"]`',
  '{"Top Navigation": "[data-ds--page-layout--slot=\"top-navigation\"]", "Main Content": "#ak-main-content", "Sidebar": "[data-ds--page-layout--slot=\"left-sidebar\"]", "Create Button": "[data-testid=\"navigation-apps-create-button\"]", "Search": "[data-testid=\"navigation-apps-search-button\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'jira',
  'unknown-jira-settings',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: jira\nscreen: unknown-jira-settings\nversion: "Cloud 2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Jira: Project Settings\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Project > Project Settings (gear icon in sidebar)\n\n## Overview\nJira project settings control the configuration of an individual project, including its workflow, issue types, permissions, notifications, and integrations.\n\n## Settings Sections\n- **Details**: Project Name, Key, Lead, Category, Avatar.\n- **Issue Types**: Configure which issue types are available.\n- **Workflow**: View and edit the workflow (statuses and transitions).\n- **Permissions**: Controls who can create, edit, transition, assign, and delete issues.\n- **Notifications**: Configure which events trigger email notifications.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Settings navigation: `[data-testid="project-settings.navigation"]`\n- Details form: `[data-testid="project-settings.details-form"]`\n- Issue types list: `[data-testid="project-settings.issue-types"]`\n- Workflow editor: `[data-testid="project-settings.workflow"]`\n- Permissions table: `[data-testid="project-settings.permissions"]`',
  '{"Settings Nav": "[data-testid=\"project-settings.navigation\"]", "Details Form": "[data-testid=\"project-settings.details-form\"]", "Issue Types": "[data-testid=\"project-settings.issue-types\"]", "Workflow Editor": "[data-testid=\"project-settings.workflow\"]", "Permissions": "[data-testid=\"project-settings.permissions\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'jira',
  'unknown-jira-search',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: jira\nscreen: unknown-jira-search\nversion: "Cloud 2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Jira: Search & Filters\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Filters (top navigation), or the global search bar\n\n## Overview\nJira''s search and filter system lets you find issues across all projects using basic text search or advanced JQL.\n\n## Search Modes\n- **Basic Search**: Text search with dropdown field filters.\n- **JQL**: `field operator value ORDER BY field ASC/DESC`\n\n## Common JQL Queries\n- `assignee = currentUser() AND status != Done`\n- `project = PROJ AND sprint in openSprints()`\n- `priority in (Highest, High) AND status != Done`\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Save Filter**: Save the current query as a reusable filter.\n- **Share Filter**: Set permissions to share with individuals or groups.\n- **Subscribe**: Get periodic email notifications when new issues match.\n- **Bulk Change**: Select multiple results and apply bulk changes.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Search input: `[data-testid="search-dialog-input"]`\n- JQL editor: `[data-testid="jql-editor-input"]`\n- Filter results: `[data-testid="search-results-table"]`\n- Save filter button: `[data-testid="save-filter-button"]`\n- View switcher: `[data-testid="search-view-switcher"]`',
  '{"Search Input": "[data-testid=\"search-dialog-input\"]", "JQL Editor": "[data-testid=\"jql-editor-input\"]", "Results Table": "[data-testid=\"search-results-table\"]", "Save Filter": "[data-testid=\"save-filter-button\"]", "View Switcher": "[data-testid=\"search-view-switcher\"]"}'::jsonb
)

