INSERT INTO vendor_wiki_pages (app, screen, content, element_selectors)
VALUES
(
  'zendesk',
  'ticket-detail',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: zendesk\nscreen: ticket-detail\nversion: "2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Zendesk: Ticket Detail Page\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Views > [View Name] > [Ticket Subject], or /agent/tickets/[ID]\n\n## Overview\nThe ticket detail page is the primary workspace for support agents in Zendesk. It shows the full conversation between the requester and support team, along with ticket metadata, internal notes, and related information.\n\n## Key Fields\n- **Requester**: The person who submitted the ticket.\n- **Assignee**: The agent responsible for the ticket.\n- **Status**: Open, Pending, On-hold, Solved, Closed.\n- **Priority**: Low, Normal, High, Urgent.\n- **Type**: Question, Incident, Problem, Task.\n- **Tags**: Freeform tags for categorization.\n- **Group**: Which team/department the ticket is assigned to.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Public Reply**: Send a response visible to the requester.\n- **Internal Note**: Add a note visible only to agents.\n- **Apply Macro**: Execute a predefined response template.\n- **Merge Tickets**: Combine duplicate tickets.\n- **Change Status**: Use the submit button (Submit as Open, Pending, Solved).\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Ticket status: `[data-test-id="ticket-status-select"]`\n- Assignee field: `[data-test-id="ticket-assignee-field"]`\n- Reply editor: `[data-test-id="omnicomposer-rich-text-container"]`\n- Submit button: `[data-test-id="submit-button"]`\n- Macro button: `[data-test-id="macro-button"]`',
  '{"Ticket Status": "[data-test-id=\"ticket-status-select\"]", "Assignee": "[data-test-id=\"ticket-assignee-field\"]", "Reply Editor": "[data-test-id=\"omnicomposer-rich-text-container\"]", "Submit Button": "[data-test-id=\"submit-button\"]", "Macro Button": "[data-test-id=\"macro-button\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'zendesk',
  'tickets-list',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: zendesk\nscreen: tickets-list\nversion: "2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Zendesk: Tickets List (Views)\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Views (left sidebar) > [View Name], or /agent/tickets\n\n## Overview\nThe tickets list page displays tickets matching a view''s filter criteria. Views are saved ticket filters that help agents organize and prioritize their workload.\n\n## Key Features\n- **Views Sidebar**: Left panel listing all available views.\n- **Ticket Table**: Sortable columns (Subject, Requester, Group, Assignee, Status, Priority).\n- **Play Mode**: Automatically cycle through unresolved tickets.\n- **View Count**: Each view shows the number of matching tickets.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Open Ticket**: Click any row to open the ticket detail page.\n- **Bulk Actions**: Select multiple tickets for bulk status, assignee, or tag updates.\n- **Edit View**: Modify filter conditions, columns, grouping, and sort order.\n- **Create View**: Build a custom view with conditions.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Views sidebar: `[data-test-id="views-sidebar"]`\n- Ticket table: `[data-test-id="ticket-table"]`\n- Play button: `[data-test-id="play-button"]`\n- Bulk action toolbar: `[data-test-id="bulk-action-toolbar"]`\n- Add view button: `[data-test-id="add-view-button"]`',
  '{"Views Sidebar": "[data-test-id=\"views-sidebar\"]", "Ticket Table": "[data-test-id=\"ticket-table\"]", "Play Button": "[data-test-id=\"play-button\"]", "Bulk Actions": "[data-test-id=\"bulk-action-toolbar\"]", "Add View": "[data-test-id=\"add-view-button\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'zendesk',
  'user-detail',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: zendesk\nscreen: user-detail\nversion: "2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Zendesk: User Detail Page\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Ticket > Requester Name (click), or /agent/users/[ID]\n\n## Overview\nThe user detail page shows all information about a Zendesk end-user or agent, including profile information, organization membership, recent tickets, and custom user fields.\n\n## Key Fields\n- **Name**: The user''s display name.\n- **Email**: Primary email address.\n- **Phone**: Phone number.\n- **Organization**: The company/organization the user belongs to.\n- **Role**: End-user, Agent, or Admin.\n- **Tags**: User-level tags.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Edit Profile**: Click fields to edit inline.\n- **Add Organization**: Link the user to organizations.\n- **Merge Users**: Combine duplicate user profiles.\n- **Suspend User**: Temporarily block from submitting tickets.\n- **Delete User**: Permanently remove and anonymize data.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- User name: `[data-test-id="user-name"]`\n- Email field: `[data-test-id="user-email"]`\n- Organization link: `[data-test-id="user-organization"]`\n- Tickets tab: `[data-test-id="user-tickets-tab"]`\n- Edit button: `[data-test-id="user-edit-button"]`',
  '{"User Name": "[data-test-id=\"user-name\"]", "Email": "[data-test-id=\"user-email\"]", "Organization": "[data-test-id=\"user-organization\"]", "Tickets Tab": "[data-test-id=\"user-tickets-tab\"]", "Edit Button": "[data-test-id=\"user-edit-button\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'zendesk',
  'organization-detail',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: zendesk\nscreen: organization-detail\nversion: "2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Zendesk: Organization Detail Page\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: User Profile > Organization Name (click), or /agent/organizations/[ID]\n\n## Overview\nThe organization detail page provides a consolidated view of a company or group in Zendesk. Organizations group users together, enabling shared ticket visibility, routing rules, and SLA policies.\n\n## Key Fields\n- **Name**: The organization''s display name.\n- **Domains**: Email domains for automatic user association.\n- **Group**: Default ticket assignment group.\n- **Tags**: Organization-level tags inherited by tickets.\n- **Shared Tickets**: Toggle for cross-user ticket visibility.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Edit Organization**: Click fields to edit inline.\n- **Add User**: Associate an existing user.\n- **Delete Organization**: Remove the org (users remain).\n- **Add Domain**: Add email domains for auto-association.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Organization name: `[data-test-id="organization-name"]`\n- Domains field: `[data-test-id="organization-domains"]`\n- Users tab: `[data-test-id="organization-users-tab"]`\n- Tickets tab: `[data-test-id="organization-tickets-tab"]`\n- Tags field: `[data-test-id="organization-tags"]`',
  '{"Organization Name": "[data-test-id=\"organization-name\"]", "Domains": "[data-test-id=\"organization-domains\"]", "Users Tab": "[data-test-id=\"organization-users-tab\"]", "Tickets Tab": "[data-test-id=\"organization-tickets-tab\"]", "Tags": "[data-test-id=\"organization-tags\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'zendesk',
  'reports',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: zendesk\nscreen: reports\nversion: "2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Zendesk: Reports (Explore)\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Reporting > Explore, or /agent/reports\n\n## Overview\nZendesk Explore is the built-in analytics and reporting tool. It provides pre-built dashboards and a query builder for custom reports covering ticket volume, response times, agent performance, and CSAT.\n\n## Pre-Built Dashboards\n- **Support Dashboard**: Ticket volume, status distribution, channel breakdown.\n- **Efficiency Dashboard**: First response time, resolution time, one-touch rate.\n- **Agent Activity**: Per-agent metrics and workload.\n- **SLA Dashboard**: Achievement rates and breach counts.\n- **Satisfaction Dashboard**: CSAT results and trends.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **View Dashboard**: Click a pre-built dashboard.\n- **Create Report**: Open the query builder.\n- **Schedule Report**: Set up recurring email delivery.\n- **Export**: Download as CSV, Excel, PDF, or image.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Reports container: `[data-garden-version]`\n- Date range picker: `[data-test-id="date-range-picker"]`\n- Dashboard tab: `[data-test-id="explore-dashboard-tab"]`\n- Query builder: `[data-test-id="explore-query-builder"]`\n- Export button: `[data-test-id="explore-export-button"]`',
  '{"Reports Container": "[data-garden-version]", "Date Range": "[data-test-id=\"date-range-picker\"]", "Dashboard Tab": "[data-test-id=\"explore-dashboard-tab\"]", "Query Builder": "[data-test-id=\"explore-query-builder\"]", "Export": "[data-test-id=\"explore-export-button\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'zendesk',
  'views',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: zendesk\nscreen: views\nversion: "2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Zendesk: Views Management (Admin)\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Admin > Workspaces > Agent tools > Views, or /agent/admin/views\n\n## Overview\nThe views management page is where admins create, edit, and organize ticket views. Views are saved ticket filters that appear in the agent sidebar.\n\n## Key Features\n- **Views List**: Shared Views and Personal Views sections.\n- **View Order**: Drag to reorder.\n- **Active/Inactive Toggle**: Hide views without deleting.\n- **View Limits**: Up to 12 shared views in the sidebar.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Create View**: Add conditions, columns, and sorting.\n- **Edit View**: Modify conditions or formatting.\n- **Clone View**: Duplicate as starting point.\n- **Deactivate View**: Toggle inactive.\n- **Set Permissions**: Control which groups can see each view.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Views admin container: `[data-test-id="views-admin-container"]`\n- Add view button: `[data-test-id="add-view-button"]`\n- View row: `[data-test-id="view-row"]`\n- Conditions editor: `[data-test-id="view-conditions-editor"]`\n- Columns editor: `[data-test-id="view-columns-editor"]`',
  '{"Views Container": "[data-test-id=\"views-admin-container\"]", "Add View": "[data-test-id=\"add-view-button\"]", "View Row": "[data-test-id=\"view-row\"]", "Conditions Editor": "[data-test-id=\"view-conditions-editor\"]", "Columns Editor": "[data-test-id=\"view-columns-editor\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'zendesk',
  'admin',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: zendesk\nscreen: admin\nversion: "2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Zendesk: Admin Center\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Gear icon in sidebar, or /agent/admin\n\n## Overview\nThe Zendesk Admin Center is the central configuration hub covering account settings, agent management, channels, business rules, workspace customization, and integrations.\n\n## Admin Sections\n- **People**: Team members, groups, roles, user/org fields.\n- **Channels**: Email, Help Center, Chat, Talk, Social Messaging.\n- **Business Rules**: Triggers, automations, macros, SLAs.\n- **Workspaces**: Contextual workspaces, dynamic content, ticket forms.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Add Agent**: People > Team Members > Add agent.\n- **Create Trigger**: Business Rules > Triggers > Add trigger.\n- **Configure SLA**: Business Rules > SLAs > Add policy.\n- **Set Up Channel**: Channels > select type > configure.\n- **Manage Apps**: Apps > Marketplace.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Admin sidebar: `#main_navigation`\n- Admin content area: `.u-posAbsolute`\n- Settings section: `[data-test-id="admin-section"]`\n- Save button: `[data-test-id="admin-save-button"]`\n- Navigation link: `[data-test-id="admin-nav-link"]`',
  '{"Admin Sidebar": "#main_navigation", "Content Area": ".u-posAbsolute", "Settings Section": "[data-test-id=\"admin-section\"]", "Save Button": "[data-test-id=\"admin-save-button\"]", "Navigation Link": "[data-test-id=\"admin-nav-link\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'zendesk',
  'dashboard',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: zendesk\nscreen: dashboard\nversion: "2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Zendesk: Agent Dashboard\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Home icon in sidebar (default landing page), or /agent/dashboard\n\n## Overview\nThe agent dashboard is the default landing page showing real-time workload overview and team activity. It displays ticket statistics, tickets requiring attention, satisfaction ratings, and recent activity.\n\n## Key Sections\n- **Ticket Statistics**: Good (within SLA), Bad (approaching/past SLA), Solved, Open counts.\n- **Requiring Attention**: Unread tickets, new replies, SLA-breaching tickets.\n- **Satisfaction**: CSAT score with Good/Bad breakdown.\n- **Recent Activity**: Feed of ticket updates and status changes.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Open Ticket**: Click any ticket to go to detail page.\n- **Switch Views**: Navigate via sidebar.\n- **Check SLA**: Review "Bad" section for urgent tickets.\n- **Start Play Mode**: Cycle through tickets in a view.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Dashboard container: `[data-test-id="agent-dashboard"]`\n- Ticket stats section: `[data-test-id="dashboard-ticket-stats"]`\n- Requiring attention list: `[data-test-id="dashboard-attention-list"]`\n- Satisfaction widget: `[data-test-id="dashboard-satisfaction"]`\n- Activity feed: `[data-test-id="dashboard-activity-feed"]`',
  '{"Dashboard Container": "[data-test-id=\"agent-dashboard\"]", "Ticket Stats": "[data-test-id=\"dashboard-ticket-stats\"]", "Attention List": "[data-test-id=\"dashboard-attention-list\"]", "Satisfaction": "[data-test-id=\"dashboard-satisfaction\"]", "Activity Feed": "[data-test-id=\"dashboard-activity-feed\"]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'zendesk',
  'unknown-zendesk',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: zendesk\nscreen: unknown-zendesk\nversion: "2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Zendesk: General Navigation\n\n## Overview\nGeneral Zendesk Support navigation covering the agent interface layout, global search, keyboard shortcuts, and tab-based multitasking.\n\n## Agent Interface Layout\n- **Top Bar**: Search, agent name/avatar, admin gear icon.\n- **Left Sidebar**: Home, Views, Reporting, Admin. Shows open ticket counts.\n- **Tabs Bar**: Open tickets as tabs for multitasking.\n- **Main Content Area**: Active view, ticket, or admin page.\n\n## Global Search\n- Press `Ctrl/Cmd + K` to open.\n- Search across tickets, users, organizations, and help center articles.\n- Use operators: `status:open`, `assignee:me`, `priority:high`.\n\n## Common Keyboard Shortcuts\n- **Ctrl/Cmd + K**: Open global search.\n- **Ctrl/Cmd + Alt + N**: Create new ticket.\n- **Tab + Return**: Submit ticket.\n- **Ctrl/Cmd + Shift + M**: Apply macro.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Top navigation: `#main_navigation`\n- Search button: `[data-test-id="search-button"]`\n- Tabs bar: `[data-test-id="tabs-bar"]`\n- Sidebar views: `[data-test-id="sidebar-views"]`\n- Main content: `[data-garden-version]`',
  '{"Top Navigation": "#main_navigation", "Search Button": "[data-test-id=\"search-button\"]", "Tabs Bar": "[data-test-id=\"tabs-bar\"]", "Sidebar Views": "[data-test-id=\"sidebar-views\"]", "Main Content": "[data-garden-version]"}'::jsonb
),
(
  'zendesk',
  'unknown-zendesk-macros',
  E'---\nlayer: vendor\napp: zendesk\nscreen: unknown-zendesk-macros\nversion: "2026"\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\nsource: "manual-mapping-v1"\n---\n\n# Zendesk: Macros & Triggers\n\n## Navigation\nAccessed via: Admin > Business Rules > Macros/Triggers\n\n## Overview\nMacros are agent-initiated templates. Triggers are event-driven automations that fire when tickets are created or updated.\n\n## Macros\n- Saved response templates applied manually to tickets.\n- Can set reply text, update fields, and add notes in one click.\n- Personal macros (agent-only) and shared macros (team-wide).\n\n## Triggers\n- Fire automatically on ticket create/update when conditions are met.\n- Execute actions like notifications, field changes, tags, webhooks.\n- Run in order; all matching triggers fire.\n\n## Common Actions\n- **Create Macro**: Admin > Macros > Add macro.\n- **Create Trigger**: Admin > Triggers > Add trigger.\n- **Organize**: Use categories and naming conventions.\n- **Reorder Triggers**: Order affects execution priority.\n\n## UI Element Selectors\n- Macros list: `[data-test-id="macros-list"]`\n- Add macro button: `[data-test-id="add-macro-button"]`\n- Triggers list: `[data-test-id="triggers-list"]`\n- Add trigger button: `[data-test-id="add-trigger-button"]`\n- Conditions editor: `[data-test-id="conditions-editor"]`',
  '{"Macros List": "[data-test-id=\"macros-list\"]", "Add Macro": "[data-test-id=\"add-macro-button\"]", "Triggers List": "[data-test-id=\"triggers-list\"]", "Add Trigger": "[data-test-id=\"add-trigger-button\"]", "Conditions Editor": "[data-test-id=\"conditions-editor\"]"}'::jsonb
)

